title: For Sale:  Custom long range Remington 700
postcontent:
I am selling my custom Remington 700 rifle. It was originally a short action .308 700 VS, and the action has been timed and trued. The bolt handle has been extended and has a larger than factory knob on it. The barrel is a Pac-Nor Super Match stainless chambered for 6.5-08 (aka .260 Rem). Twist is 1 in 8" and the contour is medium Palma. It's in an HS Precision Pro Series stock with Remington bottom metal. The scope is a Bushnell Elite 3200 10x40 with mil-dot reticle and MOA adjustments, mounted in Burris quick-release rings. This gun used to be an NRA High Power match rifle so the receiver is drilled & tapped for an iron sight base and slotted for loading with stripper clips. The muzzle is also turned down to .750" for mounting a front sight.

I also have a bunch of reloading supplies to go with the rifle. I have a Forster Ultra seating die and both full-length and neck-only Redding Type-S bushing sizing dies, along with a Redding 7mm-08 sizing die for necking down .308 cases. I have about 400 cases formed from Winchester .308 brass.  I have roughly 300 Lapua and Sierra bullets, about 1300 CCI primers, and roughly 1.75 pounds of Varget and .75 pounds of H4350. Everything is included in the asking price. If you are already reloading for a rifle caliber this is everything you need to load for this rifle. 

Face-to-face sale in the Phoenix area only.
